# DubForge Project Rules

You are contributing to DubForge.

DubForge is an offline-first AI-powered desktop application for translating, dubbing and localizing videos.

## Project Goals

Always prioritize

1. Reliability
2. Maintainability
3. Offline capability
4. Apple Silicon optimization
5. Simple user experience

## Architecture

React

↓

Electron Renderer

↓

Typed IPC

↓

Electron Main

↓

Pipeline

↓

Python Worker

↓

AI Providers

Never violate this architecture.

## Never

- Put business logic in React
- Put AI inference inside Electron
- Access filesystem from Renderer
- Couple UI to providers
- Use global mutable state

## Always

- Prefer composition
- Prefer interfaces
- Write modular code
- Keep files focused
- Write readable code over clever code

Every implementation must compile before completion.

Never leave TODO comments.

Never introduce dead code.
